This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with style transfer, which is a computer vision problem. Additionally, the use of Fully Convolutional Networks (FCNs) and VGG-16, which are commonly used in computer vision, further supports this categorization. 

The paper also involves the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. 

The balancing of content and style in style transfer is a complex problem that requires optimization, which is a common theme in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. 

The paper involves the generation of stylized images, which could fall under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper could also belong to the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it deals with the rendering of images in different styles.
